Restriction of bus termination payments
The negotiators, led by Christopher Dodd, chairman of the Senate Banking Committee, said lawmakers agreed on accountability for the financial program, protection of taxpayers from losses, closing of the rebates, and timing of the funding bill.
The new law also limits the so-called bus termination payments of directors participating in the programme and establishes a committee to oversee the fund.
