The plan also provides assistance to homeowners who have problems paying their mortgage.
The government should make new installments on the mortgages it buys, with the aim of reducing the monthly installments of debtors and allowing them to keep their homes.
Marek: Spiritual help
The proposed plan, according to David Marek, chief economist at Patria Finance, is a good idea, but it will be very difficult to implement.
'This is because it is impossible to know how and at what price the distressed assets will be bought back.
