In his series of photographs Flamenco-people, German artist Günther Bauer combines the theatricality of singers, dancers and guitarists with this lesser-known side of the masters.
Through the photographs, he presents the distinctive iconography of flamenco from different angles.
The exhibition, which is part of Flamenco Photography Month, "reflects the growing international importance of flamenco", says the artist, adding that Flamenco-people "could be anyone's character, because the viewer is struck by the images that do not represent the artists in a typical way.
