Wall Street was already in trouble at the opening, but when the Senate unexpectedly rejected a bank bailout to restore market equilibrium, it went into a deep slump.
The House of Representatives voted 228 to 205 to reject the funding requested by Treasury Secretary Henry Paulson.
The plan was rejected by nearly two-thirds of the Republicans.
"This has filtered out bad signals as Congress seems unable to approve a plan", says FTN Financial analyst Lindsey Piegza.
