The Prime Minister does not rule out a large-scale meeting, "not necessarily a summit", where "a common vision is created".
The development of the North would otherwise be in line with the principles of sustainable development.
The Northern Plan is coordinated, systematic and environmentally friendly", the Prime Minister promised.
Jean Charest described this "vision" as being in line with the vision of the Liberal prime ministers before him.
