The party congress at the end of the week proved to be an excellent platform for the Liberal president to explain the nationalist resolutions, which were approved almost without thinking, mainly on "constitutional aspirations": the Liberal Party specifically demands that "the specific character of Quebec" be recognized in the Constitution.
I also want Quebec to be able to appoint the members of the Canadian Radio-television and Telecommunications Council, and these members should have veto power over decisions made in Quebec.
